brewery.brewery_description:
TANKER - It's a beer, it's a ship!
The name TANKER was inspired by the fermentation tanks used in the beer production and massive cargo ships.

beer.beer_description: Hecking FINALLY a craft beer that tastes like, well, beer! This lovingly crafted and carefully matured beer is a keller pils, by all acounts a normal, traditional style of beer. It is light, crisp, appropriately malty and delightfully bitter. It's appearance is also delightful. Delightfully no-nonsense that is! By tradition it is unfiltered, leaving a slight, inviting haze to accentuate the beer's golden colour. Perfectly normal, perfectly beer, perfectly head and shoulders above your run-of-the-mill eurolager. Normal, not banal.

Forbidden Desire is Berliner Weisse with Prickly Pear & Blood Orange, light beer with a pale colour.
Refreshing, low alcohol content
A German wheat beer with tropical fruits with mild acidity and sweetness. Good balance of light acidity and fruit
between sweetness. The taste has a hint of kiwi, notes of mango and orange. Easy to drink sour beer.
Goes well with desserts and fruit salads, also try with goat's milk cheese.

items.badge_description: The classic Berliner Weisse is crisp, cloudy, and sour. Once the most popular beer style in Berlin, it's gained notoriety and popularity around the globe making us all proud to be Berliners. That's 15 different beers with the style of Berliner Weisse. Try 5 more for Level 4!

In a full-fledged beer revolution, Estonia is making leaps and bounds in its local craft offerings. No longer are Estonians stuck with only a handful of big beer choices. Terviseks! That's 475 different beers from a brewery from Estonia! Try 5 more to get to Level 96.

It's time to give bottle shops some love by adding them as your purchased location. That's 280 check-ins with a purchased location! Tag 5 more to get to Level 57. Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

Canning is all the rage and it's not hard to see why - travels well, more environmentally friendly, and no need to carry your bottle opener. That's 410 checkins with the serving style of Can. Try 5 more for Level 83! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast
Grab a pot and put it on your head because you're a modern day Johnny Appleseed. That's 10 different ciders. Try 5 more to unlock Level 3.

beer.beer_description:
Dark lager, low bitterness, sweet, light body, mildly roasty.
Brewed at Kalnapilio Brewery / Lithuania

The classic IPA has been given an exciting
local twist, Tanker brew for Estonian Independence day 2023. You can find hints of
local Estonian spruce tips, juniper berries
and chamomile flowers.
Spruce tips and juniper berries add light
acidity and mild sweetness to the beer.
Chamomile makes flavors lighter and
enhances the beer golden yellow color.
Northern Brewer hops add piny resinous
notes and Cascade adds spiciness and
delicate wild mint freshness.

Moderately hoppy, clean and refreshing, easily drinkable IPA.
Brewed at Kalnapilio Brewery / Lithuania

We used traditional floor malted pilsner from Czech Republic for malt complexity and a mix of noble and American hops to make our Czech style Pilsner with the signature Tanker hoppy and vibrant flavors.  Cheers!

Keep the party rolling all day long with your favorite low ABV session IPAs. That's 5 different beers with style of IPA - Session. Try 5 more for Level 2!

beer.beer_description: The essence of a traditional Sauna captured in a bottle! It is a very unusual beer, with a strong birch aroma and flavor that is very refreshing and satisfying. It’s the perfect companion to bring with you in the sauna and also for short but intense Nordic Summer. We brewed it using real birch leaves, the same ones that are used as whips in the sauna.
Electrically charged and flavorful session IPA with moderate ABV. Hook in and download the new flavor experience!

Abstraction is removing all parts that aren’t necessary to show the essential features of an idea. We brewed our version to be keep the essence of our award winning hoppy beer Hallucination. We reduced the alcohol content and the bitterness and kept all of the hoppy, juicy, freshness that we love so much. The result is a super juicy and refreshing 5.5% pale ale that is perfect as the days get warmer and longer. Cheers!

Citra on Citra on Citra. Citra Cubed. Citrazen Kane. The full 3D-experience of Citra hops in a beer. CITRA! We triple-dryhopped this beer (with Citra), meaning we took full use of hop biotransformation right at the onset of fermenting, did a 2nd dryhop at high krausen and finished things off with a classic dryhop addition at the end of fermentation. Smooth, slick, street-smart and delightfully hoppy. It's Citra!

NO NIIN - a Finnish expression worth a thousand words. Also the name of our Double Dry Hopped IPA brewed with Hallertau Blanc, Mosaic and Vic Secret hops for notes of tropical fruits, white currants and light stone fruits

Imagine the whole world beer selection as a FM broadcast band. Some frequencies just give you noise and can harm your hearing. Some provide the best signal-to-noise ratio. We made your frequency tuning a bit easier by creating the number one craft beer station to start with. Tune your mind to craft beer by starting from the very first channel. This will make your life easier when choosing another craft beer later.

Craft FM is an easy drinking 3.5% ABV beer with a refreshing citrus and grapefruit flavor. It’s perfect for relaxing and enjoying some tunes or hanging with friends.

Tardigrades are among the most resilient known animals. They are able to survive extreme conditions that would be rapidly fatal to nearly all other known life forms, such as exposure to extreme temperatures, extreme pressures, air deprivation, starvation, radiation and almost total dehydration.

Live tiny. Die never.

Hallucination is no ordinary imperial lager. It is the hoppiest beer in our lineup. A hop bomb of EPIC proportions of hops. The blend of hops gives this beer a juicy hop flavor profile and a bitter punch. Use of lager yeast makes Hallucination extremely crisp and allows the hops to shine even more than in regular IPAs.  A sturdy malt backbone helps to showcase the hops flavor without overpowering bitterness. If you love hops you can’t miss trying this one!

Take a walk on the wild side with Animal Instinct. It's a juicy IPA fermented with 100% Bruxellensis Trois yeast, the first IPA of it's kind made in Estonia. We created this beast with Van Moll Brewery from Eindhoven, Netherlands.

This beer is from the evil brewer who likes to walk on the dark side and embrace wild yeast and bacteria. Ketser is a deep red ale fermented with Brettanomyces, Lactobacillus, and Pediococcus. The result is a sour and tartly acidic beer with fruit flavours of dark cherry, plum and currant. It offers a refreshing mouthfeel with a deeply complex character. Welcome to the dark side.

Cloud Computing is a modern take on a classical wheat beer style. Soft and pale colour with a fluffy white head that resembles clouds on a long Estonian summer day. Fresh and citrusy new world hops give it a modern and fresh flavour that is very refreshing. Cloud Computing is our refreshing white IPA that is available year round.

Tanker Kraft Lager is a beautifully drinkable beer that is enjoyable all the time, especially for thirsty brewers after a hard day of work. With 5% ABV, it’s a crisp and highly drinkable Pils.  We used traditional floor malted pilsner from Czech Republic for malt complexity and a mix of noble and American hops to make our Czech style Pilsner with the signature Tanker hoppy and vibrant flavors.  Cheers!

A melody is a linear succession of musical tones that the listener perceives as a single entity. This definition can also be transformed into craft beer where all the components should match to a perfect combination. In our case, we use water, malt, yeast and hops instead of musical tones. Tanker Melody is a smooth and rich Imperial Stout with 9% ABV. It’s our tribute to the great Metal Ballads that captivate the mind and spirit. Let the gentle flavours wash over you.
Independence Pale Ale brewed to celebrate 99 and 100 years of independence of Estonia and Finalnd

Sweet and decadent aroma of mint chocolate chip ice cream. Pitch black beer with frothy brown creamy head. Chocolate, coffee, mint and roasted barley dominate the flavour at first, swallowing gives a warming hit of alcohol and bittersweet aftertaste. This is a beer designed to stand up to long and harsh winters. This beer transports you to winter wonderland!
Light bodied sour wheat beer brewed with cherries. Light red color reminds you of cherry juice.
Non Alcoholic Estonian Ale brewed with real birch leaves. Your Nordic sauna experience in a can!
Our fruit beer "Red Rain" is aged 4 months on black currant. Label is created by @awstuffxyz

This beer is not for beginners, it is intense and aggressive with massive amounts of dry hopping to stand up to the heavy grain bill. Combining the character of a strong dark beer and an aggressive West Coast style IPA, roasted character is present without going over the top. It is bitter and a bit on a dry side, but is still perfectly balanced by its sweetness. Even with your eyes closed there is no doubt that this is a black beer. Brewed in cooperation with the Metal band Herald from Estonia.

FOLK lager was made for everyone who is tired of tasteless lagers, but feel that some IPAs or DDH beers are still too much. It is nicely balanced with light amber colour, crisp and smooth lager inspired by folk music and dancing.

Moderately hoppy, clean and refreshing, easily drinkable IPA.
Brewed at Kalnapilio Brewery / Lithuania

beer.beer_description: Scotch Whisky Barrel Aged Ryewine

Rich porter with complex malt bill that gives the beer great depth and silky smoothness.  It is packed with complex chocolate and coffee flavors and has a full finish that even imperial strength beers envy. Checkmate!
Tune your mind with Sound Check before stage diving into other hardcore Tanker beers

Orange Rainbow // Blood Orange DDH IPA // 6.5% IBU 45
crisp smack of citrus, slight sourness from bloodorange, grapefruity bitterness, piney and resinous finish.
